# 🚀 Node.js Backend App with Azure Cosmos DB

This is a Node.js backend project connected to Azure Cosmos DB using the SQL API. This guide will walk you through how to clone, install, configure, and run the project locally.

---

## 📦 Tech Stack

- Node.js
- Express (optional)
- Azure Cosmos DB (SQL API)
- dotenv
- nodemon (for development)

---

## 🧾 Prerequisites

Make sure you have the following installed:

- [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) (v14 or newer)
- [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/)
- Azure Cosmos DB instance (SQL API)
  - Endpoint
  - Primary key
  - Database and container

---

## 📥 1. Clone the Repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/your-username/your-repo-name.git
cd your-repo-name
```

---

## 📂 2. Install Dependencies

```bash
npm install
```

---

## 🔐 3. Set Up Environment Variables

Create a `.env` file in the root of the project and add your Cosmos DB credentials:

```env
PORT=3000
COSMOS_ENDPOINT=https://your-account.documents.azure.com:443/
COSMOS_KEY=your-primary-key
COSMOS_DATABASE=your-database-name
COSMOS_CONTAINER=your-container-name
```

---

## 🏁 4. Run the Application

- For **development mode** (auto-restart using `nodemon`):

```bash
npm run dev
```

- For **production mode**:

```bash
npm start
```

The server will run on the port specified in the `.env` file (default is `3000`).



